A council has been criticised for launching a 'bizarre' appeal for the return of a Nazi flag that went missing from one of its offices.

The flag was given to Rowley Regis, West Midlands, after it was taken from an Italian warship sunk by the town's adopted warship HMS Tumult in 1943.

It was stored in the town hall until two years ago, when it was moved to nearby Oldbury. But yesterday it emerged the flag has gone missing.

Councillors asked the public to help find it so they can put it on display. Labour councillor Ann Shackleton said it was 'a symbol of local people's pride in their community'.

