He added: 'This Nazi flag is an important part of our history because it was captured from an Italian warship in World War II by sailors from Rowley Regis' adopted warship.

'We want what is left of our hoard back from Oldbury Council House.

'I never thought I'd ever have to say this but to whoever has our Nazi flag can we please can we have it back.'

But residents have criticised their appeal saying it is a 'disgrace' and 'a bizarre use of their time'. 

Bob Gibbins, 44, a local butcher, said: 'Have they not nothing better to do than launch an appeal to find a piece of Nazi memorabilia.

'They are hardly going to run it up the town hall flag pole when they get it back are they, considering what it represents.

